YES, the proposed patch correctly fixes the bug by ensuring that union operations are performed on the true root representatives of the sets rather than on potentially non-root nodes. The original buggy code incorrectly used the immediate parent pointers without path compression, which could lead to partial merges and disconnected components when unions were called on non-root nodes. By invoking find_set on both nodes before union, the patch guarantees that the roots are identified and merged properly, preserving the integrity of the disjoint set structure. Additionally, the patch correctly updates the parent pointers and ranks based on the root nodes, maintaining the tree's balanced nature. This change aligns with the standard union-find algorithm and resolves the issue of inconsistent representatives and split sets observed in the buggy version.
